This fork was an experiment to implement some stuff I learned online. It didn't really age well as I continued to learn, so I went back to the original code to take a new direction with the app.

---

BATS uses PHP and a PostgreSQL database to make tracking company assets easy and efficient. The work flow is designed from the ground up with the user in mind to make moves, adds, and decomissioning as easy as possible, so that there is no reason to allow your digital asset tracking to fall behind your real world deployment state.

-Required database permissions-
Each login user will need permissions such as the following:
GRANT SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public TO testuser
GRANT USAGE ON ALL SEQUENCES IN SCHEMA public TO testuser
